# Personal Manager — Codebase Overview

This document provides a detailed walkthrough of the Personal Manager codebase, mapping its architecture, database schemas, feature implementations, and system-level integrations.

---

## 1. Technology Stack
* **Language:** Kotlin (JVM 17 / SDK 34)
* **UI Framework:** Jetpack Compose with Material 3 components
* **Architecture:** Clean Architecture + MVVM (Model-View-ViewModel)
* **Dependency Injection:** Dagger Hilt
* **Local Database:** Room SQLite
* **Background Processing:** Android WorkManager & AlarmManager
* **Theme:** Customized Premium Dark Theme (Indigo-focused)

---

## 2. Architectural Structure
The project follows a standard Clean Architecture layout with a clear separation of concerns across layers.

```mermaid
graph TD
    UI[Compose Navigation / Screen Views] --> VM[ViewModels]
    VM --> UC[Use Cases - Domain Business Logic]
    UC --> Repos[Repository Interfaces]
    Repos --> RepoImpls[Repository Implementations - Data Layer]
    RepoImpls --> DAOs[Room DAOs]
    DAOs --> DB[Room Database]
    
    Service[Service Layer: Receivers & Ring Service] --> DB
    Service --> AM[AlarmManager / WorkManager]
```

